<div class='documentTop'><div>
  
  
    <h1>Rehabilitation</h1>
  
  </div></div>
  

  <div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">   
  <div>
    <p><strong>Rehabilitation benefit, which is administered by the Labour and Welfare Service, is warranted by the National Insurance Act chapter 10.</strong></p>
<p>Rehabilitation benefit is a short-term subsistence benefit that can be granted once the entitlement to sickness benefit has expired or after a person has been occupationally disabled for a continuous period of 52 weeks without being entitled to sickness benefit. To be entitled to rehabilitation benefit, recipients must be receiving active treatment with a view to improving their work capacity. The same activity requirement applies as during the sickness benefit period. </p>
<p>If the person in question is in an employment relationship, he/she shall, together with the employer, identify measures at the workplace that can help to ensure that the employment relationship continues. If such measures at the workplace are unsuccessful, or the person is not in an employment relationship, it must be considered as early as possible whether assistance from the Labour and Welfare Service is required.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
